@startuml
left to right direction

' Explicitly declare use cases so the renderer treats this as a Use Case diagram
actor Researcher
actor Technician
actor Student
actor "Visiting Collaborator" as Visitor
actor "Maintenance Team Member" as Maintenance
actor "Catering Staff" as Catering
actor "External Contractor" as Contractor

actor "Security Officer /\nControl Room Operator" as Security
actor "Duty Manager /\nFacility Manager" as DutyMgr
actor "Safety Officer" as Safety
actor "Area Supervisor" as Supervisor
actor "Auditor / Compliance" as Auditor

rectangle "Access Management System" {

  usecase "Request Emergency Access" as UC_RequestEA
  usecase "Grant Emergency Access\n(Break-glass)" as UC_GrantEA
  usecase "Manual Override Door/Zone" as UC_Override
  usecase "Suspend/Cancel Permit/Access" as UC_Suspend
  usecase "Record Justification &\nIncident Reference" as UC_Justify
  usecase "Post-incident Review / Audit" as UC_Audit
}

' General roles can request emergency access
Researcher  --> UC_RequestEA
Technician  --> UC_RequestEA
Student     --> UC_RequestEA
Visitor     --> UC_RequestEA
Maintenance --> UC_RequestEA
Catering    --> UC_RequestEA
Contractor  --> UC_RequestEA

' Privileged roles can grant/override/suspend
Security   --> UC_GrantEA
DutyMgr    --> UC_GrantEA
Safety     --> UC_GrantEA
Supervisor --> UC_GrantEA

Security --> UC_Override
DutyMgr  --> UC_Override

Security   --> UC_Suspend
DutyMgr    --> UC_Suspend
Safety     --> UC_Suspend
Supervisor --> UC_Suspend

' Audit / review stakeholders
Auditor    --> UC_Audit
Security   --> UC_Audit
DutyMgr    --> UC_Audit
Safety     --> UC_Audit
Supervisor --> UC_Audit

' Strong audit obligations: justification is mandatory
UC_GrantEA  ..> UC_Justify : <<include>>
UC_Override ..> UC_Justify : <<include>>
UC_Suspend  ..> UC_Justify : <<include>>

' Reviews occur after exceptional actions (optional extension relationship)
UC_Audit ..> UC_GrantEA  : <<extend>>
UC_Audit ..> UC_Override : <<extend>>
UC_Audit ..> UC_Suspend  : <<extend>>
@enduml